# Routing & Layout Rules

## Scope
Apply these rules to every file in:
- `src/pages/**/*.jsx`
- `src/router.jsx`
- `src/config/routes.js`
- `src/layouts/`

---

## Rule 1 — Every Page Must Be Wrapped in MainLayout

`MainLayout` injects `<TopBar>`, `<Navbar>`, and `<Footer>` automatically.
Never add them manually inside a page file.

```jsx
// ✅ Correct
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout';

export default function ServicesPage() {
  return (
    <MainLayout>
      <ServicesHero />
      <OurServicesGrid />
      <WhyChooseUsSection />
      <FAQAccordion items={serviceFaqs} />
      <GetInTouchForm />
    </MainLayout>
  );
}

// ❌ Wrong — never render Navbar or Footer inside a page
export default function ServicesPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <Navbar />        {/* Remove — injected by MainLayout */}
      <ServicesHero />
      <Footer />        {/* Remove — injected by MainLayout */}
    </>
  );
}
```

---

## Rule 2 — All Routes Defined in routes.js

All route path strings live in `src/config/routes.js` as named constants.
Never hardcode a URL string in `<Link to="">` or `navigate()`.

```js
// src/config/routes.js
export const ROUTES = {
  HOME: '/',
  ABOUT: '/about',
  PRODUCTS: '/products',
  PRODUCT_DETAIL: '/products/:id',
  SERVICES: '/services',
  CONSULTANTS: '/services/consultants',
  MAINTENANCE: '/services/maintenance',
  INSPECTIONS: '/services/inspections',
  DISTRIBUTION_GRID: '/industries/distribution-grid',
  CITY_INFRASTRUCTURE: '/industries/city-infrastructure',
  AGRICULTURE: '/industries/agriculture',
  SOFTWARE: '/solutions/software-application',
  CONTACT: '/contact',
  NEWS: '/news',
  NOT_FOUND: '*',
};
```

```jsx
// ✅ Correct
import { ROUTES } from '@/config/routes';
<Link to={ROUTES.PRODUCTS}>View All Products</Link>
<Link to={ROUTES.PRODUCT_DETAIL.replace(':id', product.id)}>View</Link>

// ❌ Wrong — never hardcode URL strings
<Link to="/products">View All Products</Link>
<Link to={`/products/${product.id}`}>View</Link>
```

---

## Rule 3 — Adding a New Page (Always Follow All 3 Steps)

**Step A — Add route constant to `src/config/routes.js`:**
```js
export const ROUTES = {
  ...
  NEW_PAGE: '/new-page-path',   // ← add here
};
```

**Step B — Register in `src/router.jsx` with lazy loading:**
```jsx
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';
const NewPage = lazy(() => import('@/pages/NewPage'));

// Inside the router:
<Route path={ROUTES.NEW_PAGE} element={<NewPage />} />
```

**Step C — Create the page folder with index.js:**
```
src/pages/NewPage/
├── NewPage.jsx
├── index.js          ← export { default } from './NewPage';
└── components/
```

---

## Rule 4 — All Pages Use Lazy Loading

```jsx
// src/router.jsx
import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';

const HomePage     = lazy(() => import('@/pages/Home'));
const AboutPage    = lazy(() => import('@/pages/About'));
const ProductsPage = lazy(() => import('@/pages/Products'));
// ... all pages lazy-loaded
```
